        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Scheme of Providing Assistance to Encourage Farmers for Adoption of Organic Farming&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to encourage farmers to adopt organic farming by offering financial incentives for certification, registration, and input costs. It helps maintain soil fertility, supports biological input management, and promotes traditional knowledge. \n",
        "benefits_md": "**Name of the Component****Standard of Assistance****Minimum Time Limit (in Years) for Reclaiming  Benefits**Registration/ CertificationAssistance for Certification/Registration fees 75% from GOPCA and 50% assistance in Certification fees with other certifying Body;  Upto Maximum  ₹2,000/- per HectareEvery yearInputInput subsidy of ₹5,000/- per Hectare for Certified farmEvery yearResidue testingPer sample Assistance upto ₹1,0000/-Every year<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme has been introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Dept., Gujarat. It aims to promote organic farming by providing financial assistance to farmers for certification, input subsidies, and residue testing. ",
